items.name: ComfyUI - Diva Styles Workflow
items.description:
This workflow includes a Styles Expansion that adds over 70 new style prompts to the SDXL Prompt Styler style selector menu.

For this Styles Expansion workflow to work you need to have "SDXL Prompt Styler" installed: https://github.com/twri/sdxl_prompt_styler

I also highly recommend the "ComfyUI-Manager": https://github.com/ltdrdata/ComfyUI-Manager.git If you're missing any nodes it will let you know which ones you're missing and will give you a quick one-click install option for the missing nodes.

This workflow and the included JSON file adds 70+ visual styles and art styles to the SDXL Prompt Styler menu. It took some research on the different art styles to know how to prompt for each style and I learned a lot. They're not perfect, as many styles are new to me and I had to make educated guesses based on the style's descriptions on how to build the prompt scripts for them. So they might not be 100% true to the styles, but they do add a nice amount of artistic variety!

This expansion and it's 70+ visual styles (as well as modifying a workflow for it) took a few hours to compile and create, so if you have a minute please leave a rating for this. I'd very much appreciate it! :)

If you enjoy this or get some creative fun out of it please consider donating: https://ko-fi.com/3diva It would really help to motivate me to keep creating new content for you guys.

~ Diva

items.name: XL Art Supply
items.description:
XL Art Supply

No need to buy me a coffee, but do rate / favorite / post few images :)

Settings I used for model / version showcase

Sampling Steps: 40-50

CFG scale: 7-20

Sampling Method: DPM++ 2M Karras 

Ratio:1024x1024

Negative:

(worst quality, low quality), blurry, noisy, lowres, signature, watermark, username

No inversions / loras / scripts / whatsoever were used to increase generated images quality. Refiner was not used. Upscaled after generation in extras tab using 4x-UltraSharp & R-ESRGAN 4x+ at 40% visibility.

Merge info / procedure

First few merges were done using regular weight sum: A*(1-alpha)+B*alpha / Add difference:A+(B-C)*alpha / Triple sum:A*(1-alpha-beta) methods & normal calculation mode. Further one switched to sum Twice (A*(1-alpha)+B*alpha)*(1-beta)+C*beta keeping the regular calculation until few good candidates were present. Later on experimented further with train difference calc mode on new merge batches. I do not recall exact recipe and merging order, but these were the ones that went in to the merges - DreamShaper / Copax TimeLessXL / DucHaiten-AIart / [Lah] Mysterious / ProtoVision / SDVN6 / SDVN7 / SDXL_Niji

items.name: 【Art Style】Weri
items.description:
如果找到了正确的方法，训练这个画风还是很简单的

在Anything和NAI上表现良好（建议直接使用NAI即可），在其他底模上画风拟合性能未知，有兴趣可以自己尝试一下。

没怎么测试在其他大模型上的泛化性，尝试在NAI下，与自训练的白圣女模型共同出图，得到了一张Sample。可以看到在我自己的人物lora上展现了良好的泛化性。即使是练的稍微差一点的江江也能完全驾驭的住

建议与easynegative一起使用，提示词加入highres（不加应该也不会有多大影响）

It may be quite easy if you find the right way to train it.

Good performance was achieved on Anything series model and NAI model (recommend using NAI). The performance of art style is unknown on other base models, you can try it yourself if interested.

Lack testing generalization on other base models. I have attempted using NAI model, and got a sample image with my own trained Cecilia character lora, which seems really nice. Even my poorly-trained Suzushima Arisu character lora can work well too.

I recommend to use with easynegative embedding. ‘highres’ should be added in prompts (as trigger), and it’s ok if you don’t add it in.

items.name: InkPunk XL
items.description:
InkPunk LORA was designed for those who crave the gritty, edgy look of inkpunk art, but also want the intelligence and coherence that SDXL LORA offers. It's the best of both worlds, blending unique artistic style with cutting-edge tech, to give you something genuinely new and engaging.

Details: Currently in alpha state, this is the Lora version of the SDXL InkPunk Style Model. Pretty good all around with text2img and img2img, but has difficulty with some animals. Setting the Lora weight to 0.5 is a good starting point, and adjusting the CFG can also help produce better results. With Img2img, you can also change the denoising strength as well, but it's good to start with 0.5 as well. Raising the denoising number can allow more of the style to shine through in situations where it's being shy.

Prompting: Nearly all images in the gallery are going to be using prompts which start with "inkpunk style illustration" and end with the lora itself.

items.name: CrystaliTI
items.description:
This is a TI embedding for Stable Diffusion v1.5 that adds a crystal and/or gem effect to your generated images - everything from spiky crystals to flat stained glass The crystal/gem effect is based on realistic jewels and crystal growths rather than cartoon/manga style.

The inspiration for this TI was the 1985 scifi novel “Sentenced to Prism” by Alan Dean Foster.

Good pun, better book :-)

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sentenced_to_Prism

Training was run on the base Stable Diffusion v1-5-pruned.ckpt [e1441589a6].

My personal preference is for surreal/fantasy images, so that’s what this TI is aimed at.

All of the showcase gens are done with

Vendo Photorealistic 2 v1

https://civitai.com/models/83490/vendo-photorealistic-2

or

Vendo Universal v1

https://civitai.com/models/119469/vendo-universal

I’ve tried this TI on a dozen or so other models and it seems to work reasonably with them all, but I prefer the Vendo ones at the moment.

This TI works with short and long prompts. Short prompts are quite overwhelming with total crystal conversion. Long prompts vary between adding crystalline effects globally, to just adding jewellery/gems here and there. For strength adjustment I usually just move the TI token forwards or backwards in my prompts. When I’ve tried emphasis syntax, values from about 0.85 to 1.15 seem to be OK.

The usual SD v1.5 issues apply: far-away faces are not great, hands are variable, eyes can be odd, limbs can be doubled/missing/merged. Using your favorite negatives will help, as will inpainting of course.

The only extra problem I’ve been getting with this TI is a tendancy to orange for shorter prompts / higher emphasis. Not sure why because the training images don’t seem to have too much orange in them. Whatever the reason, adding orange to the negative prompt on a case-by-case basis mostly sorts it out.

items.name: Piggyback | LoRA
items.description:
Recommended values: 0.7-1

The trigger words are: carrying, piggyback

Note:

  • For a boy and a girl, it is difficult to interpret two completely different outfits, so it is advised to prompt an outfit that would make sense for both individuals, i.e.: school uniform, formal outfit, swimsuit, etc.

  • When generating a boy and a girl,he Lora is likely to generate a child being carried, although it can generate adults as well.

Enjoy!

If you like the model, you are free to share your creations, I really like seeing everyone's results! :)
